  "text": "CGEN in Equation (21) can be generated by an n-row, 2-column cluster state with n output qubitsthe last column is the (unmeasured output), and with n XY plane measurement angles \u03b1 i , see Figure  6 . We denote the set U CGEN = {CZ 1,2 ...CZ n\u22121,n (HZ(\u03b1 1 + m 1 \u03c0) \u2297 .... \u2297 HZ(\u03b1 n + m n \u03c0))}. As seen in [10, 15] , showing that Equation (22) holds amounts to showing that the set U CGEN is a universal set in U (2 n ) [18, 19, [CITATION_1] . Our result about the universality of U CGEN can be summarized in the following theorem.",
